<h2>In-class Lab 13.2</h2>
<ol type="I">
<li class="row0">
<p>Exercise 1</p>
<ol type="1">
<li class="row0">
<p>
In this lab, we are going to implement the Login System with Sessions example
at the end of Unit 13. You should download the Unit 13 PHP scripts from
Blackboard to your virtual machine or lab computer if you have not already done
so. We will modify the <b>login.html</b> , <b>auth.php</b> and <b>protected.php</b>
scripts in this lab.
</p>
</li>
</li><li class="row0">
<p>
If using your Linux VM, create directory <b>lab13</b> under your
<b>/var/www/labs</b> directory, if it does not exist.
Otherwise create directory <b>lab13</b> under
the document root of whatever web server you are using.
On the MATC Windows lab computers that will be: <b>C:\xampp\htdocs</b>
If using XAMPP on your external USB drive it will probably be: <b>E:\xampp\htdocs</b>
</p>
</li>
<li class="row1">
<p>
Copy the <b>login.html</b> , <b>auth.php</b> and <b>protected.php</b> scripts
to the lab13 directory you created.
</p>
</li>
<li class="row1">
<p>
First, make sure the 3 scripts work on your virtual machine or lab computer,
exactly like they worked when the instructor demonstrated them in class.
</p>
<p>
If they do not work correctly, consult your instructor.
</p>

<li class="row0">
<p>
Modify the scripts so that the username and password that can successfully
log in are both the username you use to connect to the class server (your
first initial and last name).
</p><p>
Make sure you also change the message displayed to the user, so they will
know the correct login name.
</p>
</li>
<li class="row1">
<p>
Change the "protected" content on the <b>protected.php</b> page, so that it
contains some "secret and interesting" information about your favorite book,
movie, T.V. show, etc.
</p></li>
<li class="row1">
<p>
Test your revised version of the Login application to be sure it works correctly,
and show it to your instructor.
</p></li>
</ol>
<p><hr width="75%" /></p>
</li>
</ol>
